The Ondo state chapter of the All Progressives Congress (APC), has dismissed the rumours making the rounds on social media that it has postponed primaries for local government election indefinitely, saying it was untrue. The party, in a statement by its spokesman, Alex Kalejaye, said “the story is untrue, embarrassing, and never emanated from the state secretariat.” Kalejaye affirmed that the party had a credible and rancour-free primaries across the eighteen local government areas, early last month, and has since submitted the names of its candidates to the Ondo State Independent Electoral Commission (ODIEC), as required by the electoral law. He said, “We are therefore miffed that anyone, for whatever reason, would go the press with such a unfounded claim”. The party spokesman urged all stakeholders and party members to disregard the misapprehension and misleading story. According to him, “The party is fully ready to participate in the local government election as scheduled by the ODIEC, and would not give serious attention to futile distortions aimed at creating disaffection within its fold, and promote disenchantment in the process.” 